A healthcare technology and solutions firm, Infodemics has launched an online application that connects a database of medical professionals to manage risk communications in the healthcare industry. Speaking at a mentorship closing ceremony on Regional Programme Support to Pandemic Prevention in ECOWAS Region (RPPP) in Abuja yesterday, the team lead of Infodemics, Dr Nestor Inimgba, said in this era of information technology polarisation, there is a need to fully tap into its potentials even though some communities are yet to start adapting to current realities. Inimgba said that the infodemics.com is an easy to use interface that assists proactively the management of health-related issues such as plagues, using its integrated SMS, eMail, Unstructured Supplementary Service Data (USSD), Interactive Voice Response (IVR) and leased shortcode media to communicate risk to the last mile. According to him, ‘’Infodemics is a one-stop risk communication solution. It started after GIZ/ECOWAS sponsored West African health risk hackathon in November 2018 in Abuja. ‘’We are rolling out solutions especially to English speaking West Africa to get early feedback before a public data.’’
Speaking earlier at the event, the head, Surveillance and Epidemiology, Nigerian Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), Elsie Ilori, applauded the ingenuity of the programme, saying the centre deals with data and would consider such programme because they require an effective feedback mechanism to tackle healthcare challenges, most especially where there are language, cultural and religious barriers. Adding that the Nigerian government places a premium on the healthcare of the citizenry, hence funds are available for the agency to carry out their obligations with support from foreign donors and specialists.